.TH HIDLOOM-KEYTEXT 1 "@HIDLOOM_VERSION@" "HIDloom" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hidloom-keytext \- send ASCII text as key tap events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hidloom-keytext
[\fB--socket\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--hold-us\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB--gap-us\fR \fIN\fR]
\fITEXT\fR [\fITEXT\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hidloom-keytext
maps supported ASCII characters to keyboard HID tap events and sends them to
logicd. It is a small scripting helper, not a full text input method.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --socket PATH
Unix socket path. The default is the logicd key event socket.
.TP
.B --hold-us N
Hold duration for each tap.
.TP
.B --gap-us N
Gap between taps.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command help.
.SH ESCAPES
Supported escapes include \fB\\n\fR, \fB\\r\fR, \fB\\t\fR, \fB\\\\\fR,
\fB\\"\fR, and \fB\\xNN\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hidloom-key (1),
.BR hidloom-ctrl (1),
.BR logicd (8)
.br
